<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1841] Add clientside githooks to do basic commit validation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1841</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Last week I made a commit and I made an error: The commit message was not fully according to the right format.&lt;br/&gt;
To avoid future mistakes I propose we introduce validation to the commit message by using the git hooks.&lt;br/&gt;
These can be run in two places: client side and server side.&lt;br/&gt;
This ticket focuses on the client side hooks. If we decide to add this also to the server side that must be a separate ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12965821">AVRO-1841</key>
            <summary>Add clientside githooks to do basic commit validation</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21140&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="5" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/resolved.png" description="A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.">Resolved</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="nielsbasjes">Niels Basjes</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="nielsbasjes">Niels Basjes</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Sat, 7 May 2016 12:31:58 +0000</created>
                <updated>Wed, 11 May 2016 12:48:49 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 10 May 2016 22:18:21 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>1.8.1</fixVersion>
                                    <component>build</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15275213" author="nielsbasjes" created="Sat, 7 May 2016 12:41:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Basic fact: Because of the security risks any client side git commit hooks must be installed after the &lt;tt&gt;git clone&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
This patch simply adds a new command to the build.sh script to install the required git scripts to do the client side verification. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can choose to implicitly run this step as part of each of the build.sh commands, for now I wrote it as a separate command.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15275779" author="rdblue" created="Sun, 8 May 2016 22:48:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the Parquet project, we have a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/parquet-mr/blob/master/dev/merge_parquet_pr.py&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;commit script&lt;/a&gt; that ensures the commit message follows conventions. The drawback is that it requires contributions to be pull requests and Avro has traditionally used patches. It also makes it harder to make a small change and commit rather than asking the contributor to make it. It does avoid these issues though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15276106" author="nielsbasjes" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 08:33:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t quite understand what you are saying.&lt;br/&gt;
My intention with this patch is to simply add a simple aid to us to avoid mistakes.&lt;br/&gt;
If you see a better way please explain what direction you think is best.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15276529" author="rdblue" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 15:44:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m just pointing out another way I&apos;ve seen it done, I don&apos;t have a strong opinion on how to do this. The commit hook sounds like a reasonable way to go, but I&apos;m not sure many people would use it since commit hooks in git are self-enforced.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15278529" author="nielsbasjes" created="Tue, 10 May 2016 17:39:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I understand there are multiple ways of achieving this. Shall I commit this one or not?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15278581" author="rdblue" created="Tue, 10 May 2016 18:00:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15279104" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 10 May 2016 22:17:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 51a260a27f3b2d6a046d2ed005eeff0dc7fa6e76 in avro&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nielsbasjes&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nielsbasjes&quot;&gt;Niels Basjes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
